<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 3:49PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Sheridan County through 415 PM MDT...
At 349 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grenora, or 24 miles southeast of Plentywood, moving southeast at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Dagmar and Coalridge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
